get.description: Providers are cloud infrastructure and service providers from which all cloud prices are derived. You can think of example Providers as being AWS, GCP, Cloudflare or Datadog. Currently, Vantage only supports a single provider of AWS but over time more will be added. Use this endpoint to retrieve a provider id for other API calls.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page of results to return.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The amount of results to return. The maximum is 1000

get.description: Return all Services. Examples of Services are EC2 for AWS. This endpoint will return all Services by default but you have the ability to filter Services by Provider using the optional query parameter documented below.

parameters.name: provider_id
parameters.description: Query services for a specific provider. e.g. aws

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page of results to return.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The amount of results to return. The maximum is 1000

get.description: Return available Products for a Service. For example, with a Provider of AWS and a Service of EC2, Products will be a list of all EC2 Instances. By default, this endpoint returns all Products across all Services and Providers but has optional query parameters for filtering listed below.

parameters.name: provider_id
parameters.description: Query by Provider to list all Products across all Services for a Provider. e.g. aws

parameters.name: service_id
parameters.description: Query by Service to list all Products for a specific provider service. e.g. aws-ec2

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: Query by name of the Product to see a list of products which match that name. e.g. m5a.16xlarge

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page of results to return.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The amount of results to return. The maximum is 1000

get.description: Return available Costs for the specified Cost Report and optional time period. If no time period is specified it will return all available costs for the report.

parameters.name: start_date
parameters.description: Query costs by the first date you would like to filter from. ISO 8601 Formatted - 2021-07-15 or 2021-07-15T19:20:48+00:00.

parameters.name: end_date
parameters.description: Query costs by the last date you would like to filter to. ISO 8601 Formatted - 2021-07-15 or 2021-07-15T19:20:48+00:00.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page of results to return.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The amount of results to return. The maximum is 1000

parameters.name: grouping
parameters.description: Group the results by specific field(s). Valid groupings: account_id, billing_account_id, charge_type, cost_category, cost_sub_category, provider, service, tag:<tag_value>, region, folder_id, resource_id. If providing multiple groupings, be sure to use the following syntax: grouping[]=provider&grouping[]=service&grouping[]=account_id

name.description: The common name of the provider.

name.description: The common name of the service. Usually an abbreviation.

description.description: The full name of the service.

category.description: The category of the cloud product

name.description: The common name of the product.

service_id.description: A unique slug for the service the product belongs to.

provider_id.description: A unique slug for the provider the product belongs to.

details.description: An object of metadata about the product.

unit.description: The unit in which the amount is billed.

region.description: The region the price is specific to.

rate_type.description: The part of the product the price applies to. (compute, transfer, etc..)

amount.description: The amount of money this specific product price costs.

title.description: The title of the cost report.

earliest_cost_date.description: The date and time, in UTC, the report was created. ISO 8601 Formatted.

latest_cost_date.description: The date and time, in UTC, the report was created. ISO 8601 Formatted.

created_at.description: The date and time, in UTC, the report was created. ISO 8601 Formatted.

workspace.description: The name of the workspace the report is a part of.

total.description: The sum of all amounts of costs for the entire report for the requested period.

currency.description: The currency both the total and cost amount values are represented in. e.g. USD
